        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 4:04AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 403 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southeast of Mc Curtain, moving southeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Bokoshe...                        Red Oak...
Panola...                         Mccurtain...
Cameron...                        Summerfield...
Robbers Cave State Park...        Fanshawe...
Kinta...                          Mc Curtain...
Wilburton...                      Poteau...
Wister...                         Lake Wister State Park...
Stigler...                        Shady Point...
Panama...                         Heavener...
Howe...                           Hodgen...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
west central Arkansas...and southeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
